Codex Usage Overlay
===================

A small Windows desktop overlay that shows Codex rate-limit usage and pacing guidance.

It reads the same Codex Desktop usage endpoint used by the account menu, then shows:

- remaining 5-hour usage
- remaining weekly usage
- reset times
- a pacing hint such as "Use more", "Slow down", or "On track"

See docs/usage-overlay.md for setup and build instructions.

Privacy
-------

The app reads the local Codex Desktop auth file at ~/.codex/auth.json so it can call the Codex usage endpoint.
It does not display or log the token.

Development
-----------

Install dependencies:

    npm install

Run locally:

    npm start

Run tests:

    npm test

Build Windows installer:

    npm run dist:win

Release Model
-------------

Installer EXE files should be attached to GitHub Releases, not committed to git history.

